    "body": "I think the only remaining 'evil blues' on [visualisation.html](http://pandas.pydata.org/pandas-docs/dev/visualization.html) are for `scatter_matrix` and `lag_plot`. They both use the `scatter` method from matplotlib. Some observations:\n- The reason is because `c='b'` is hardcoded in the matplotlib scatter function (see [here](https://github.com/matplotlib/matplotlib/blob/master/lib/matplotlib/axes/_axes.py#L3140)), and thus not following the color in the settings (rcParams['patch.facecolor']). So changing this settings does not affect the scatter plot.\n- I think this can be seen as a bug/inconvenience in matplotlib => maybe issue there\n- We could try to circumvent this in pandas:\n  - explicitly set color or facecolor equal to to `matplotlib.rcParams['patch.facecolor']`\n  - however, I don't directly see how to do that without getting into problems when the user also sets a color in the functions (`scatter_matrix(..., c= ..)` because this is then leads to 'keyword argument repeated'\n"
  },
