    "body": "@jtratner you mean just `kwds.setdefault('c', matplotlib.rcParams['patch.facecolor'])`?\n\n@cpcloud Would you add a `color` keyword? Because at the moment, there is no color keyword in [`scatter_matrix`](https://github.com/pydata/pandas/blob/master/pandas/tools/plotting.py#L203). If you want to change the color of the markers, you just have to use the passing of `c` to the matplotlib `scatter` via `**kwds`. \nBut that's a seperate issue I think, because als eg `bootstrap_plot`, `lag_plot`, `autocorrelation_plot`, have no `color` keyword, but it depends on the underlying matplotlib function if setting `color` would work or not.\n"
  },
