    "body": "@jorisvandenbossche `c` or `color` is accepted by `scatter`, it's actually already \"there\" since `kwds` is passed to `scatter`, so you can use either `c` or `color` when you're calling `scatter_matrix`. The problem is that you break that \"feature\" of calling `scatter` if you choose either `c` or `color` so you need to account for the case where someone would pass both (pathological, but possible). I would enforce the `color` keyword parameter.\n"
  },
